FT  08 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Cost control behind advance at Hewitt
Close attention to productivity and control of costs helped Hewitt Group,
the industrial ceramics and refractories maker, to stage a recovery.
In the first half of 1992 pre-tax profit came to Pounds 411,000, including a
Pounds 98,000 gain on the sale of a fixed asset.
Turnover amounted to Pounds 3.74m (Pounds 3.58m). Earnings per share were
7.3p (3.8p) and the interim dividend goes up to 1.25p (1p).
